                  <handDesc><!--ACHTUNG! first HandNote comes from writing system in Ethiospare. the others are one for each CHANGE OF HAND-->
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <ab type="script">Fine, but irregular.</ab>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red</seg>The Ms. was written by the same hand as the one of AP-008. The handwriting is similar, but not identical to that of AP-038.<date>Late 17th-18th century</date>
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">The handwriting is characterized by a fine script with tendency to right-sloping and angularly shaped letters. <!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h3" script="Ethiopic">
Some distinctive features appear throughout the Ms.:<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h4" script="Ethiopic">
-	archaic form of 'one' (፩, triangular upwards-oriented)<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h5" script="Ethiopic">
-	short hairlines extending horizontal elements of some letters (esp., የ and ይ )<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h6" script="Ethiopic">
-	strongly pronounced shading (esp. መ, በ, ን, ዘ, የ, ደ)<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h7" script="Ethiopic">
-	some letters appear in a forked shape (esp. ኃ, ር, ን, ገ, ጋ)<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h8" script="Ethiopic">
-	the hook vowel marker of ቱ is attached at the upper part of the downstroke<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h9" script="Ethiopic">
-	ክ shows a very distinct vowel marker<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h10" script="Ethiopic">
-	the right loop of ሠ (in all vowel orders) is of a very small size<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h11" script="Ethiopic">
-	letters ደ and ይ appear in a triangular shape<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h12" script="Ethiopic">
-	ጥ is written with long curves.<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h13" script="Ethiopic">
Though the handwriting appears very irregular throughout the Ms. (cp., fols. 32v-33r) it is the same as the one of AP-008 and also similar to that of AP-038.<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                  </handDesc>
